io.github.utk003.util.misc.annotations

Annotation Type ScheduledForRelease


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=SOURCE)
 @Target(value={TYPE,METHOD,FIELD,CONSTRUCTOR,PACKAGE})
 @ScheduledForRelease(inVersion="v3.0.0")
public @interface ScheduledForRelease
    Indicates that the given class, method, field, etc. will be officially "released" in the future.

    Any item marked by this annotation is not quite ready to be considered an official part of the API but is planned be released by the specified version. This annotation plays a role half way between no annotation and the @ApiStatus.Experimental annotation: The API is not quite as volatile as indicated by @ApiStatus.Experimental, but still possibly more volatile than a "fully released" feature.

    This annotation can specify planned version of release, if known. For example: 

     @ScheduledForRelease
 public class LoremIpsum {
     @ScheduledForRelease(inVersion = "v0.0.0")
     public static void main(String[] args) {
     }
 }

    If the inVersion fields is not defined, this annotation can serve as an open-ended marker for an upcoming release. In such a case, the annotation can be updated in the future with a specific version.

    The removal-equivalent of this annotation is @ApiStatus.ScheduledForRemoval.

    Since:
    3.0.0
    Version:
    July 20, 2021
    Author:
    Utkarsh Priyam (utk003)
